This course is designed and built by subject matter and industry experts in the field. Every course has been created to equip you with theoretical and practical knowledge and real-life problem-solving skills to be successful in an entry-level job. This course forms part of a series designed to jumpstart your career in computer support, equipping you with the knowledge and skills necessary for both hardware and software support. 

In this course, you will be introduced to the fundamentals of computer systems. Youâ€™ll explore vital components such as the CPU, memory, storage, and peripherals. You'll learn how these elements interact with the operating system, covering CPU processes, memory management, and the significance of device drivers. Additionally, you'll gain insight into essential concepts defining the hardware and software relationship, ensuring a thorough understanding of system functionality.

After completing this course, you will be able to: 

Identify the critical components of computer systems, encompassing hardware elements such as CPU, memory, storage devices, input/output devices, and peripherals. 

Describe the interaction between computer system components and the operating system, including how the CPU processes instructions, memory management, and the role of device drivers.

Discuss the essential concepts that define the relationship between hardware and software, fostering a comprehensive understanding of system functionality.
